1
00:01:38,330 --> 00:01:41,050
[The Demon Hunter's Romance]

2
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:44,009
[Episode 29]

3
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,120
Young master.

4
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:06,920
You're awake.

5
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:07,890
How are you?

6
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,150
Are you feeling better?

7
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:10,550
Is there any discomfort?

8
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:17,690
Your clothes

9
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:18,590
are inside.

10
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,130
I'll go get them for you.

11
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,980
Young master, please have a seat.

12
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:32,190
I've tidied up

13
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:33,470
your clothes for you.

14
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:35,120
Please rest easy and recover.

15
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,870
Our master

16
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:37,420
knows a bit about medicine.

17
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:38,910
You were trapped in a fire.

18
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:39,750
It was a neighbour from the village

19
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,460
who rescued you and brought you here.

20
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:43,390
You can stay here and rest assured.

21
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:49,850
There are more.

22
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,650
There are these too.

23
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,400
Young master, you must be starving.

24
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,840
There's still hot food on the stove.

25
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,800
I'll bring it to you.

26
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,000
Please wait a moment.

27
00:03:31,540 --> 00:03:32,220
Man Ying.

28
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:42,740
What are you looking at?

29
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:43,940
You seem so absorbed.

30
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:46,380
Mr. Bai's farewell letter.

31
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,010
Farewell letter?

32
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,020
He said in a couple of days,

33
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:51,620
he'll be leaving Guangping.

34
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,310
You've seen him?

35
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:55,470
I have.

36
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,280
Did you take action?

37
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:00,120
Am I really just

38
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:01,810
a cold-blooded,

39
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,500
ruthless killer in your eyes?

40
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:05,400
No.

41
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,510
Then why is he suddenly leaving

42
00:04:07,510 --> 00:04:08,910
when everything's fine?

43
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:12,390
Why are you so concerned about him?

44
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:15,570
I just think

45
00:04:16,269 --> 00:04:17,470
he's not a bad person.

46
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,459
He doesn't deserve

47
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:19,459
a miserable fate.

48
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,630
You've only met him a few times,

49
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,680
and you already think he's not bad?

50
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,140
He's not bad to begin with.

51
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:31,980
Yesterday,

52
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,590
I went to Fa'en Temple.

53
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,040
So you're saying

54
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,450
there are two Mr. Bai?

55
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:41,890
One is the snake demon Chilian,

56
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,380
and the other is Xingxian?

57
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:44,990
That's right.

58
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,530
No wonder

59
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,870
sometimes I felt

60
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,130
he was very close to me.

61
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,540
The one you're familiar with

62
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,850
should be Xingxian.

63
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,860
Surprising, isn't it?

64
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,820
I didn't expect it either.

65
00:04:59,450 --> 00:05:01,340
A snake demon who had never done evil

66
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:02,140
actually killed two people

67
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:03,250
for her sake,

68
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,320
and even used the snake slough

69
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:06,180
to help her change her appearance

70
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:08,620
to evade the authorities' investigation.

71
00:05:09,710 --> 00:05:12,040
This snake demon treats Xingxian so well.

72
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,640
No matter how well, killing is still wrong.

73
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,760
I'm not trying to make things difficult for him.

74
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:24,620
It's just that demons live longer

75
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:25,950
and are more powerful.

76
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:28,000
Ordinary people can compare to them.

77
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,350
If they want to kill,

78
00:05:30,290 --> 00:05:31,120
a mortal's life hangs

79
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,630
on their whim.

80
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:34,950
So it's hard for them to see human life

81
00:05:34,950 --> 00:05:36,430
as something precious.

82
00:05:37,950 --> 00:05:38,920
Since he had a reason

83
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,320
to kill the first person,

84
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,310
it's very likely that, in the future,

85
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:43,560
he uses the same reason

86
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,890
to kill a second person,

87
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,730
even a third.

88
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,880
So we absolutely cannot let it be

89
00:05:48,180 --> 00:05:49,900
and allow him to act as he pleases.

90
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,550
No one is born a sage,

91
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:52,970
and no one

92
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:55,030
can always distinguish right from wrong.

93
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:56,380
Let alone a demon.

94
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:57,850
Alright, alright.

95
00:05:57,850 --> 00:05:58,940
Hurry up and eat.

96
00:06:01,390 --> 00:06:02,470
You talk too much.

97
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,130
You're even more naggy than my father.

98
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,310
Sir.

99
00:06:20,710 --> 00:06:21,710
Are you going out?

100
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,480
Aren't we leaving in a couple of days?

101
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,540
I thought I'd go visit the neighbours

102
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,680
to bid farewell.

103
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,580
What about you?

104
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:37,090
Are you going to Liushui Pavilion today?

105
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:38,000
I have to.

106
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,310
After all, I've known the owner for many years.

107
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:41,240
Before leaving,

108
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,140
I should at least say goodbye.

109
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:44,880
Then I'll be going now.

110
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,630
Be careful on your way.

111
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:47,560
Come back early.

112
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:59,400
[Puji]

113
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:20,630
Your faithful devotee, Xingxian, is grateful for the Bodhisattva's blessings,

114
00:07:20,630 --> 00:07:22,720
and have come specially to fulfil my vow.

115
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,220
Although the act of solving my troubles

116
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:26,680
did not come directly from the Bodhisattva,

117
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,800
without you,

118
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:29,480
I would never have had the courage

119
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,480
to speak out all that was in my heart,

120
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:33,560
nor the wisdom

121
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:36,070
to understand where my true heart lies.

122
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:36,870
There would never have been

123
00:07:36,870 --> 00:07:38,159
the Xingxian of today.

124
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,240
Your great kindness,

125
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:42,960
your faithful devotee will never forget.

126
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,960
This is a small token of my appreciation.

127
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,770
I hope you won't refuse it, sir.

128
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:55,190
I can't accept it.

129
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,360
Please accept it.

130
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,409
All these years,

131
00:07:58,510 --> 00:08:00,080
if it weren't for Mr. Bai's support,

132
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,210
my Liushui Pavilion

133
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:03,160
wouldn't have the reputation it has today.

134
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,190
Just consider this small token of appreciation

135
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:04,950
as some

136
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:06,610
extra money for your journey.

137
00:08:06,950 --> 00:08:07,830
I hope, sir,

138
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:09,440
you won't refuse it.

139
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:18,260
Although I'm just an ordinary person,

140
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:20,270
I can still tell that your Qin playing is excellent.

141
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:22,310
As you travel the world in the future,

142
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:23,270
more people

143
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:24,510
will hear your music.

144
00:08:24,730 --> 00:08:26,000
I'm happy for you,

145
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:27,240
and for those people as well.

146
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,070
I hope he dies.

147
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,880
The reason he's still alive

148
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,400
is because I saved him, isn't it?

149
00:08:35,780 --> 00:08:36,470
Mr. Bai.

150
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,049
You must be busy.

151
00:08:43,570 --> 00:08:45,250
I won't take up more of your time.

152
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:45,850
Well then,

153
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,430
I'll use tea instead of wine

154
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:49,360
to wish you all the best

155
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:50,940
and a safe journey.

156
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:52,760
Then, let's bid farewell here.

157
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:55,490
Your faithful devotee, Xingxian,

158
00:08:55,490 --> 00:08:57,370
once made three wishes here.

159
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,750
Now they have all come true.

160
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,600
I shouldn't be greedy anymore.

161
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,200
But now,

162
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:07,510
I have one last wish.

163
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:11,000
However, this time,

164
00:09:12,470 --> 00:09:13,870
I won't ask for your help.

165
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:17,350
Please forgive me, Bodhisattva.

166
00:09:18,490 --> 00:09:19,370
This time,

167
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,140
I'll do it myself.

168
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,270
Sir,

169
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,960
why are you here?

170
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,660
I've been waiting for you.

171
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:03,270
Don't you like the apricot blossom wine

172
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:05,700
from that tavern at the foot of the mountain?

173
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,100
I specially bought some.

174
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,600
Oh, right,

175
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:10,770
there's also some marinated duck.

176
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:13,630
It'll be perfect to go with the wine when we get back.

177
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:14,850
Let's go.

178
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:26,890
Sir,

179
00:10:27,190 --> 00:10:28,590
the dishes are all ready.

180
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,580
It looks so sumptuous.

181
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:33,620
We're leaving tomorrow,

182
00:10:33,690 --> 00:10:35,550
so let's have a good meal tonight.

183
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,480
Come,

184
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,030
try this.

185
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:43,150
I heard this is a cooking method

186
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:44,720
that originated from Jiangnan.

187
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:45,630
The duck meat is tender,

188
00:10:45,630 --> 00:10:47,290
and even the bones are crispy.

189
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:54,670
Not bad.

190
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:58,880
When we get to Jiangnan,

191
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,380
we'll have the even more authentic ones.

192
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,370
Alright.

193
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:05,270
When I said goodbye to Shopkeeper Song today,

194
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:06,050
he mentioned

195
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:07,930
several Qin masters in Jiangnan,

196
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,000
and even drafted a few visiting cards for me.

197
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,330
When we reach Jiangnan,

198
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:14,600
let's visit and learn from them together.

199
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:18,070
Your Qin playing has a unique style.

200
00:11:18,370 --> 00:11:19,830
It's clear and melodious,

201
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,570
gentle but not cloying.

202
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:22,870
I really like it.

203
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,880
I don't think I've asked before,

204
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:30,390
who did you learn to play the Qin from?

205
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:36,090
It was my mother.

206
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,400
She was originally a Qin master.

207
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:45,520
Although she was making a living in the marketplace,

208
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,250
she was quite well-known

209
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:49,090
and respected.

210
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:50,910
Later,

211
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:54,240
she fell in love at first sight

212
00:11:54,270 --> 00:11:55,670
with my merchant father.

213
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,390
Two years after their marriage,

214
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:58,390
I came into being.

215
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:01,810
Unfortunately, the good times didn't last long.

216
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,690
When I was six years old,

217
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:05,810
my father's business failed.

218
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:06,840
He then took out his frustration

219
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,390
on my mother.

220
00:12:09,110 --> 00:12:11,090
He constantly berated her for her humble origins,

221
00:12:11,090 --> 00:12:13,150
saying she couldn't help the family.

222
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,570
As time went on,

223
00:12:15,310 --> 00:12:17,240
my mother stopped playing the Qin.

224
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:19,290
Eventually,

225
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:21,870
my younger brother was born.

226
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:24,320
My mother seemed to believe

227
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,120
that my brother was a lucky star.

228
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,080
She thought that

229
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,530
the family's fortune got better

230
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:31,990
all because of my brother.

231
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,320
So she joined my father

232
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:35,630
in belittling me,

233
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:39,030
and forbade me from touching the Qin again.

234
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,840
But you know what?

235
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:48,240
I really wanted to play the Qin again.

236
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:51,590
Don't cry.

237
00:12:52,930 --> 00:12:53,720
You'll definitely be able to

238
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,520
play the Qin again in the future.

239
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:58,510
I will.

240
00:13:01,350 --> 00:13:03,550
Heaven has given me this wretched life,

241
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,250
not so I could wallow in self-pity.

242
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:09,120
I will do what I want to do,

243
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,500
and play the Qin I want to play.

244
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,510
Sir.

245
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:33,750
Sir,

246
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,120
why aren't you drinking?

247
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,650
WIth the moonlight weeping

248
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,420
I shall play a tune.

249
00:13:45,370 --> 00:13:46,770
Would you like to listen?

250
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:50,030
Alright.

251
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:59,860
♫The sun rises, shining bright♫

252
00:14:00,670 --> 00:14:04,580
♫Its brilliance blazing♫

253
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:08,730
♫By chance, I glimpse my loved one♫

254
00:14:09,370 --> 00:14:13,280
♫Reflected in my eyes♫

255
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:17,990
♫The moon ascends, glowing white♫

256
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:23,000
♫Its glow serene and clear♫

257
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:27,990
♫Again, I glimpse her♫

258
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:32,890
♫Reflected in my eyes♫

259
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,720
I told you before

260
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:42,250
that this was a lost old tune.

261
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:44,660
Actually, I lied to you.

262
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,270
This piece

263
00:14:47,610 --> 00:14:49,010
was composed by me,

264
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,820
written for an old friend.

265
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,730
♫Torturous lovesickness♫

266
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:55,170
I caught a glimpse of my loved one,

267
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:58,230
♫Yet mutual confession is even harder♫

268
00:14:55,850 --> 00:14:57,380
and my heart leaps with joy.

269
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,150
She haunts my soul and dreams,

270
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:00,270
and lingers in my thoughts ever since.

271
00:14:59,170 --> 00:15:05,140
♫Drifting like a willow in the wind, yearning for a good ending♫

272
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:03,200
Because my heart is bound,

273
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,910
no matter the storm or gale,

274
00:15:05,570 --> 00:15:11,230
♫Side by side, we share a gaze too deep for words♫

275
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,880
harsh frost or cold snow,

276
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:10,120
I just want to see her once,

277
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:12,630
even if it's just a glimpse from afar.

278
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:17,990
♫Keep silent with no regrets♫

279
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:17,150
Although I have to endure countless hardships,

280
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:18,480
I'll never be tired of it.

281
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:24,520
♫Share days and nights with you♫

282
00:15:24,050 --> 00:15:24,880
Xingxian.

283
00:15:24,810 --> 00:15:30,950
♫In exchange for a lifelong deep love♫

284
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:27,910
Are you glad

285
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,200
to have known me?

